# UI: no disclaimer spam / TMI

Dashboards and analytics screens should stay readable for busy clinical and ops users.

## Do not

- Repeat the same caveat in **section captions**, **subheadings**, **tooltips**, **inline alerts**, and **table helper text** (e.g. “not hospital-wide totals”, “loaded/filtered subset only”, “not SPC”, “not clinical probability”, “not mechanistic causation”, “not official DNS rate” on every block).
- Chain multiple **“ไม่ใช่…” / “ไม่ได้…”** sentences in one place; that reads like defensive boilerplate and confuses more than it protects.

## Do instead

- State **what the number or chart is** in the title or one short line (units, period, definition).
- Put rare edge cases or methodology in **one** place if needed: a single help/tooltip entry, glossary doc, or release note — not scattered through the page.
- Prefer **neutral labels** (“ตัวเศษ (IPD D–I)”, “รายเดือน”) over repeated scope lectures.

When adding copy, ask: “Did we already say this two scrolls up?” If yes, **delete the duplicate**.
